/cast 2<br>
/g Remedy on %t<br>
/cast 2<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I do NOT like to put sit and stand in my macros.  I always remember to stand up, and sometimes it's not good to sit right back down after a heal.<br>
<br>
For my shaman, I have a Cann macro though, looks like this:<br>
<br>
/sit off<br>
/cast 8<br>
/pause 3, /cast 8<br>
/pause 20<br>
/sit on<br>
<br>
That macro allows me to sit long enough to be considered medding but still get up and cann every so often.  the /pause 3, /cast 8 is to catch fizzles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7A3412><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uaarich.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aarich</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 193<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(6/13/02 11:49:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Button</span><hr size=1> I agree sitting in a macro isnt a good idea, but I oftentimes bot my cleric/chanter, and forgetting to stand on occasion has resulted in fatalities - so I added it to my macro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#581212><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uqueudini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queudini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(6/17/02 12:21:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.houston.rr.com/mcherry/images/Kermit%20the%20Frog.jpg HEIGHT=126 WIDTH=108></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Button</span><hr size=1> Well I ended up with the following and it works great.<br>
<br>
/doability 4<br>
/cast 8  <br>
/g ----&lt;{Casting (whatever heal here) on %t}&gt;-----<br>
/cast 8 <br>
<br>
I really liked the idea of the /cast 8 twice, it has helpped a lot when I fizzle, and I use it on other buttons also, like my root.  I will be using this on my Chanters buttons now too.  Thanks alot for the advice and help. <p><p><BR><img border=0 src="http://home.houston.rr.com/mcherry/images/Signature%20Pictures/Sig.%20Dolls/new-sig-small-version.gif"width="324"height="216"><BR>
